<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1938-05-21T06:35:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1938-05-21T06:35:00-05:00" n="614" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d614">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">891.6363 Amiranian/58: Telegram</note>
                            <head><hi rend="italic">The Chargé in Iran</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Engert</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss></hi></head>
                            <opener>
                                <dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Teheran</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1938-05-21T15:00:00+03:25">May 21, 1938—3
                                    p.m.</date><lb/>[Received May 21—1:05 p.m.]</dateline>
                            </opener>
                            <p>49. My 48, May 18, 2 p.m.<note n="43" xml:id="d614fn43">Not
                                    printed.</note> Informal and verbal notification was given by
                                the company this morning to the Director of the Petroleum Bureau.
                                The latter is reported to have said that this would make it
                                practically impossible for any American interests ever again to
                                obtain petroleum or any other concessions in Iran.</p>
                            <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Engert</hi></signed></closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>